    "notes": "Brings up a local A2A vendor ecosystem for dev/demo. The registry on port 8800 aggregates each mock agent's /.well-known/agent.json card. Each vendor agent runs on its own local_port (8811-8828) and exposes a JSON-RPC (and gRPC where bound) /a2a endpoint plus a /healthz probe. In mock mode all upstream calls are stubbed with deterministic fixtures, push notifications are delivered to the internal webhook sink at http://localhost:8801/webhooks, and OAuth2/api_key/mtls flows are short-circuited by the local dev CA. Start everything with run_command, or bring up the docker compose stack; individual agents can be launched with their per-card mock_command. Production 'url' values remain authoritative for staging/prod and are never contacted in local mode.",
